											<span id="DataList1__ctl2_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>I did some work to the forums today (yesh, i had to work in VB)&nbsp;.. anyway...&nbsp; When you go to your forum, you will no longer have connection to the main Guild Wizard forum.&nbsp; That`s something that has been confusing, to say the least for some guilds.&nbsp; Now, when you go to your forum by clicking the button, you are taken to your forum with no links to the Main Forum List on Guild Wizard`s forum.&nbsp; Anyone who used the forums should know what I am talking about, it was annoying as hell :)</P>
<P>Another change, I finally got around to locking forums of non-subscribing guilds.&nbsp; Prior to this patch, guilds were able to setup a forum during the trial period, add all their members and continue to use the forum even though their trial was finished.&nbsp; This was due to the fact that I didnt have time to sift through the forum code to find where I can disable.&nbsp; Anyway, the forums are still `there` , just disabled till you subscribe.&nbsp; </P>
<P>If I have more time today, I will continue playing with the forum code.&nbsp; I am going to put a link-back to your main guild wizard site so its not such a pain in the butt to get back.&nbsp; Then I will look into the sticky posts and deleting issues!</P></font></span>
