											<span id="DataList1__ctl5_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>Well, well, well.. it seems that Verant has some Guild Manager player lists coming out in TAB delimited and others in Comma Delimited.&nbsp; What this means is the seperator between the values in each column is either a TAB (5 spaces) or a Comma (,)&nbsp; .. makes a big difference when guys like me are trying to write software to read it :)&nbsp; hehe</P>
<P>Anyway, most people were using Comma from what I can see, but a few people have emailed me with log files in TAB format.&nbsp; Guild Wizard will now read either format.&nbsp; Hell, you can even have a file with half and half if you want ! (why anyone would, is beyond me).</P>
<P>Subscriptions seem to be integrating smoothly... i have had only 1 minor problem with a guilds status not changing.&nbsp; I re-wrote my paypal web-service a bit and there definatly shouldnt be any problems.&nbsp; Your status is updated within 2 minutes of PayPal notifying my webservice.</P></font></span>
